NixOS is a Linux distribution which uses the Nix package manager to
manage all constituents of the system, which includes configuration
files, services, environment variables, users accounts, and even the
kernel. See [Nix Package Manager - Main
Page](//Main Page Package Manager) to read about how to use this package
manager and its benefits.

